-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529402\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kwj1665702926465.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kwj1665702926465.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kwj1665702926465.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kwj1665702926465\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Dropping Referential Integrity in the Database\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have implemented database referential control and you want to revert to having Uniface do that, you can generate and run an SQL script to drop referential integrity.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__context_w2702ab1b5b1_w2703ab1b5_w2704ab1\">\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23516e1_d23517e1_d23518e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Generate the SQL scripts for dropping referential integrity. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wly1665702737011.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1665702737011.html\" title=\"For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database.\">Generate Referential Integrity Scripts</a>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23519e1_d23520e1_d23521e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity by adding or removing the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23522e1_d23523e1_d23524e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the scripts to drop referential integrity constraints\n                  (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>). </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23525e1_d23526e1_d23527e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Load the data into the tables.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23528e1_d23529e1_d23530e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the script to validate relationship constraints ( (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_validateReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>).).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23531e1_d23532e1_d23533e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23534e1_d23535e1_d23536e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the script to enforce referential integrity constraints (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_createReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23537e1_d23538e1_d23539e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the connector for database referential integrity support again. For more\n               information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wly1665702737011.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wly1665702737011.html\" title=\"For some database systems, you can have the DBMS (instead of Uniface) manage referential integrity. To do so you need to generate referential integrity scripts and have the database administrator execute those scripts in the target database.\">Generate Referential Integrity Scripts</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23540e1_d23541e1_d23542e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the application assignment file to configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity. You will need to add or remove the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23543e1_d23544e1_d23545e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the resulting SQL script to specify your database name.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23546e1_d23547e1_d23548e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the script to drop referential integrity constraints\n                  (<span class=\"ph filepath\">*_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql</span>). </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"kwj1665702926465__li_d23552e1_d23553e1_d23554e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the connector for Uniface referential integrity support.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529402\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529402\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Dropping Referential Integrity in the Database Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Dropping Referential Integrity in the Database If you have implemented database referential control and you want to revert to having Uniface do that, you can generate and run an SQL script to drop referential integrity. Generate the SQL scripts for dropping referential integrity. See Generate Referential Integrity Scripts . Configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity by adding or removing the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS. Execute the scripts to drop referential integrity constraints ( *_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql ). Load the data into the tables. Run the script to validate relationship constraints ( ( *_validateReferentialIntegrity.sql ).). Investigate and resolve any reported violations of referential integrity. Execute the script to enforce referential integrity constraints ( *_createReferentialIntegrity.sql ). Configure the connector for database referential integrity support again. For more information, see Generate Referential Integrity Scripts . Edit the application assignment file to configure the connector to enable Uniface referential integrity. You will need to add or remove the relevant connector option. See the connector documentation for your DBMS. Edit the resulting SQL script to specify your database name. Execute the script to drop referential integrity constraints ( *_dropReferentialIntegrity.sql ). Configure the connector for Uniface referential integrity support. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}